3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* smtpd_sasl_proto 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* Postfix SMTP protocol support for SASL authentication
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include "smtpd.h"
10/* #include "smtpd_sasl_proto.h"
11/*
12/* void smtpd_sasl_auth_cmd(state, argc, argv)
13/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
14/* int argc;
15/* SMTPD_TOKEN *argv;
16/*
17/* void smtpd_sasl_auth_extern(state, username, method)
18/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
19/* const char *username;
20/* const char *method;
21/*
22/* void smtpd_sasl_auth_reset(state)
23/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
24/*
25/* char *smtpd_sasl_mail_opt(state, sender)
26/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
27/* const char *sender;
28/*
29/* void smtpd_sasl_mail_reset(state)
30/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
31/*
32/* static int permit_sasl_auth(state, authenticated, unauthenticated)
33/* SMTPD_STATE *state;
34/* int authenticated;
35/* int unauthenticated;
36/* DESCRIPTION
37/* This module contains random chunks of code that implement
38/* the SMTP protocol interface for SASL negotiation. The goal
39/* is to reduce clutter of the main SMTP server source code.
40/*
41/* smtpd_sasl_auth_cmd() implements the AUTH command and updates
42/* the following state structure members:
43/* .IP sasl_method
44/* The authentication method that was successfully applied.
45/* This member is a null pointer in the absence of successful
46/* authentication.
47/* .IP sasl_username
48/* The username that was successfully authenticated.
49/* This member is a null pointer in the absence of successful
50/* authentication.
51/* .PP
52/* smtpd_sasl_auth_reset() cleans up after the AUTH command.
53/* This is required before smtpd_sasl_auth_cmd() can be used again.
54/* This may be called even if SASL authentication is turned off
55/* in main.cf.
56/*
57/* smtpd_sasl_auth_extern() records authentication information
58/* that is received from an external source.
59/* This may be called even if SASL authentication is turned off
60/* in main.cf.
61/*
62/* smtpd_sasl_mail_opt() implements the SASL-specific AUTH=sender
63/* option to the MAIL FROM command. The result is an error response
64/* in case of problems.
65/*
66/* smtpd_sasl_mail_reset() performs cleanup for the SASL-specific
67/* AUTH=sender option to the MAIL FROM command.
68/*
69/* permit_sasl_auth() permits access from an authenticated client.
70/* This test fails for clients that use anonymous authentication.
71/*
72/* Arguments:
73/* .IP state
74/* SMTP session context.
75/* .IP argc
76/* Number of command line tokens.
77/* .IP argv
78/* The command line parsed into tokens.
79/* .IP sender
80/* Sender address from the AUTH=sender option in the MAIL FROM
81/* command.
82/* .IP authenticated
83/* Result for authenticated client.
84/* .IP unauthenticated
85/* Result for unauthenticated client.
86/* DIAGNOSTICS
87/* All errors are fatal.
88/* LICENSE
89/* .ad
90/* .fi
91/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
92/* AUTHOR(S)
93/* Initial implementation by:
94/* Till Franke
95/* SuSE Rhein/Main AG
96/* 65760 Eschborn, Germany
97/*
98/* Adopted by:
99/* Wietse Venema
100/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
101/* P.O. Box 704
102/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
103/*
104/* TLS support originally by:
105/* Lutz Jaenicke
106/* BTU Cottbus
107/* Allgemeine Elektrotechnik
108/* Universitaetsplatz 3-4
109/* D-03044 Cottbus, Germany
110/*--*/

144/* smtpd_sasl_auth_cmd - process AUTH command */
145
146int smtpd_sasl_auth_cmd(SMTPD_STATE *state, int argc, SMTPD_TOKEN *argv)
147{
148 char *auth_mechanism;
149 char *initial_response;
150 const char *err;
151
152 if (var_helo_required && state->helo_name == 0) {
153 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_POLICY;
154 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "503 5.5.1 Error: send HELO/EHLO first");
155 return (-1);
156 }
157 if (SMTPD_STAND_ALONE(state) || !smtpd_sasl_is_active(state)
158 || (state->ehlo_discard_mask & EHLO_MASK_AUTH)) {
159 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
160 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "503 5.5.1 Error: authentication not enabled");
161 return (-1);
162 }
163 if (SMTPD_IN_MAIL_TRANSACTION(state)) {
164 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
165 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "503 5.5.1 Error: MAIL transaction in progress");
166 return (-1);
167 }
168 if (smtpd_milters != 0 && (err = milter_other_event(smtpd_milters)) != 0) {
169 if (err[0] == '5') {
170 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_POLICY;
171 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "%s", err);
172 return (-1);
173 }
174 /* Sendmail compatibility: map 4xx into 454. */
175 else if (err[0] == '4') {
176 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_POLICY;
177 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "454 4.3.0 Try again later");
178 return (-1);
179 }
180 }
181#ifdef USE_TLS
182 if (var_smtpd_tls_auth_only && !state->tls_context) {
183 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
184 /* RFC 4954, Section 4. */
185 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "504 5.5.4 Encryption required for requested authentication mechanism");
186 return (-1);
187 }
188#endif
189 if (state->sasl_username) {
190 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
191 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "503 5.5.1 Error: already authenticated");
192 return (-1);
193 }
194 if (argc < 2 || argc > 3) {
195 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
196 smtpd_chat_reply(state, "501 5.5.4 Syntax: AUTH mechanism");
197 return (-1);
198 }
199 /* Don't reuse the SASL handle after authentication failure. */
200#ifndef XSASL_TYPE_CYRUS
201#define XSASL_TYPE_CYRUS "cyrus"
202#endif
203 if (state->flags & SMTPD_FLAG_AUTH_USED) {
204 smtpd_sasl_deactivate(state);
205#ifdef USE_TLS
206 if (state->tls_context != 0)
207 smtpd_sasl_activate(state, VAR_SMTPD_SASL_TLS_OPTS,
208 var_smtpd_sasl_tls_opts);
209 else
210#endif
211 smtpd_sasl_activate(state, VAR_SMTPD_SASL_OPTS,
212 var_smtpd_sasl_opts);
213 } else if (strcmp(var_smtpd_sasl_type, XSASL_TYPE_CYRUS) == 0) {
214 state->flags |= SMTPD_FLAG_AUTH_USED;
215 }
216
217 /*
218 * All authentication failures shall be logged. The 5xx reply code from
219 * the SASL authentication routine triggers tar-pit delays, which help to
220 * slow down password guessing attacks.
221 */
222 auth_mechanism = argv[1].strval;
223 initial_response = (argc == 3 ? argv[2].strval : 0);
224 return (smtpd_sasl_authenticate(state, auth_mechanism, initial_response));
225}
226
227/* smtpd_sasl_mail_opt - SASL-specific MAIL FROM option */
228
229char *smtpd_sasl_mail_opt(SMTPD_STATE *state, const char *addr)
230{
231
232 /*
233 * Do not store raw RFC2554 protocol data.
234 */
235#if 0
236 if (state->sasl_username == 0) {
237 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
238 return ("503 5.5.4 Error: send AUTH command first");
239 }
240#endif
241 if (state->sasl_sender != 0) {
242 state->error_mask |= MAIL_ERROR_PROTOCOL;
243 return ("503 5.5.4 Error: multiple AUTH= options");
244 }
245 if (strcmp(addr, "<>") != 0) {
246 state->sasl_sender = mystrdup(addr);
247 printable(state->sasl_sender, '?');
248 }
249 return (0);
250}
251
252/* smtpd_sasl_mail_reset - SASL-specific MAIL FROM cleanup */
253
254void smtpd_sasl_mail_reset(SMTPD_STATE *state)
255{
256 if (state->sasl_sender) {
257 myfree(state->sasl_sender);
258 state->sasl_sender = 0;
259 }
260}
261
262/* permit_sasl_auth - OK for authenticated connection */
263
264int permit_sasl_auth(SMTPD_STATE *state, int ifyes, int ifnot)
265{
266 if (state->sasl_method && strcasecmp(state->sasl_method, "anonymous"))
267 return (ifyes);
268 return (ifnot);
269}
